node.text: Tune is as we go live with media personality/actress and global sensation @JoelahNoble . From the UK to NYC sneakers and creativity have brought her around the world. Listen as she sits with host by @FrescoBK to let us into her world.

node.text: A curator of connectivity and community @nickcho_ checks in with Stadium Goods to talk sneakers, being a Korean Dad and understanding through connection.

node.title: Celebrating AAPI Heritage month with “Your Korean Dad” @NickCho_

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Stadium Goods in Stadium Goods. May be a closeup of footwear.

node.text: One of a kind. The two sets of laces, layered Swooshes, and double tongues found on Sacai’s Nike Blazer Low “Magma Orange” are unlike any other design modification ever applied to the vintage low-top basketball shoe.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Stadium Goods in Stadium Goods. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: The modified, stitched-down tongue on Union’s Air Jordan 4 “Desert Moss” isn’t the only update applied to the retro basketball shoe. The model’s mesh base, suede panels, and speckled rope laces are all new facets of its design, as well.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Stadium Goods in Stadium Goods. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: The summer may be winding down, but with the Women’s Air Jordan 1 High Zoom Comfort “Lemon Twist,” you can still wear footwear inspired by the season’s warm undertones well into fall. Now if only you could bring summer’s weather with you, too.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Stadium Goods in Stadium Goods. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: Good money no matter the setting, our Stadium Goods Amphibians Shorts excel as swim shorts in the summer and are reliable in the early fall when the weather is still moderately warm.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Stadium Goods in Stadium Goods. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: Jordan Brand closes out its Summer 2021 collection with a final salute to the warm weather season on the breezy Women’s Air Jordan 1 High “Seafoam,” which happens to be available in full family sizing.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Stadium Goods in Stadium Goods. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: Plants and nature are the vibe behind Nike’s Women’s Air Force 1 Low “Indigo,” one of several botanical-themed colorways that finds the former basketball shoe in a new hemp-like construction.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Stadium Goods in Stadium Goods. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: Can you spot the differences between the Travis Scott x Fragment x Air Jordan 1 Low and High? On the low, the trio gives the shoe a cream Swoosh, black overlays, and a white leather base. The high-top dons a black Swoosh amid other modifications.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Stadium Goods in Stadium Goods. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: Summer won’t last forever, but that doesn’t mean you have to stop wearing shoes decked out in warm colors. Bring the Women’s Nike Dunk Low “Lime Ice” with you on all your fall adventures in the months ahead.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Stadium Goods in Stadium Goods. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: One of several Summer 2021 colorways of the always-on-point lifestyle shoe, the adidas Yeezy Boost 350 V2 “Mono Cinder” takes cues from the silhouette’s “Cinder” colorway of 2020 while introducing a new semi-translucent mesh construction.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Stadium Goods in Stadium Goods. May be an image of 3 people, people standing, footwear, brick wall and indoor.

node.text:
Need to grab a few more staples for your Fall wardrobe? Shop our back to school deals now.
.
.
.
Enjoy 15% off select styles under stadiumgoods.com/sale through 9am EDT 8/23. All sales are final. Promotional offers and discounts do not apply to shipping and handling, or taxes. Offer may not be combined with other offers.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Stadium Goods in Stadium Goods. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: From telephone booths to figurines to tees, the mediums in which KAWS has used to spread his art have varied over the years. Some would argue that his best work came when he turned the Air Jordan 4 into a work of sneaker art in 2017.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Stadium Goods in Stadium Goods. May be an image of footwear.

node.text: This is family business. Popular styles from Kanye West’s signature shoe collection with adidas, like the Yeezy Foam Runner MX in “Cream Clay,” are available in full family sizing. That means everyone can look fly for the rest of summer and beyond.
